How the canvas is generated
gridGeometry.ts

contains generateGridPositions(shape, gridSize)
supports shapes like hexagon, spiral, circle, wave, organic, square
returns 3D positions for each grid cell
WebGLCanvas.tsx

creates a Three.js scene
places a mesh at each position returned by the generator
matches purchased blocks by gridX/gridY
renders owned blocks and available slots in the same scene
Engine.tsx

merges campaign-owned blocks with empty grid slots
handles selection, purchase modal, color choice, and messages